36:39.000 --> 36:42.000
On every green leaf, there are millions of

36:42.000 --> 36:45.000
sub-microscopic little one-man factories

36:45.000 --> 36:49.000
turning out more sugar than all the ships and railroads in the world could carry.

36:49.000 --> 36:54.000
And the head man of each factory is a little green molecule called chlorophyll,

36:54.000 --> 36:59.000
the only engineer with a know-how about this still secret life process.

36:59.000 --> 37:02.000
Chlorophyll is so small and so secretive

37:02.000 --> 37:05.000
