50:27.000 --> 50:32.000
But our engineers can't turn the wheels of industry on little wafers.

50:32.000 --> 50:34.000
They'll have to build efficient generators

50:34.000 --> 50:37.000
that spread out over acres, even square miles,

50:37.000 --> 50:40.000
to compete with the cheap, cold, and oil still available to us.

50:40.000 --> 50:43.000
And the doctor, what about atomic power?

50:43.000 --> 50:45.000
Oh, great hopes for it, of course.

50:45.000 --> 50:48.000
Especially now, since atomic plants can make their own fuel

50:48.000 --> 50:50.000
with so-called breeder reactors.

50:50.000 --> 50:53.000
Some even dream of imitating the stars,

50:53.000 --> 50:56.000
getting power from hydrogen fusion.

50:56.000 --> 51:01.000
But if dreams fail, the answer must be sun power from our Mr. Sun.

51:01.000 --> 51:06.000
What if you don't find ways to use my free sunshine for fuel?

51:06.000 --> 51:09.000
Then the machine age is over.

51:12.000 --> 51:14.000
We'll have to go back to muscle power

51:14.000 --> 51:19.000
and the half-billion population that muscle power alone can support.

51:27.000 --> 51:29.000
But that will never happen.

51:29.000 --> 51:31.000
Oh, no, why not?

51:31.000 --> 51:36.000
Because man's greatest power source is his mind.

51:36.000 --> 51:39.000
God gave him that, not you.

51:39.000 --> 51:45.000
Without taking a step, he can travel faster and farther than any animal.

51:45.000 --> 51:49.000
Without even getting wet, he can out-swim any fish.

51:49.000 --> 51:54.000
Without a fell on him, he can fly faster and higher

51:54.000 --> 51:57.000
and farther than any eagle.

52:00.000 --> 52:05.000
He can send his eyes and ears hundreds of miles into space

52:05.000 --> 52:08.000
where he's never even been.

52:11.000 --> 52:14.000
And his pride opened the secret of the atom,

52:14.000 --> 52:17.000
which he's never even seen.

52:17.000 --> 52:19.000
When his fuel's run low,

52:19.000 --> 52:23.000
man's mind and imagination will meet the challenge

52:23.000 --> 52:27.000
and invent undreamed of ways to use the free sunlight

52:28.000 --> 52:31.000
God showers down upon him.

52:31.000 --> 52:37.000
Just remember, somebody must love you very much.

52:37.000 --> 52:42.000
That planet that you live on is not like all the rest.

52:42.000 --> 52:46.000
You're blessed with just the right size,

52:46.000 --> 52:50.000
the right temperature, the right atmosphere,

52:50.000 --> 52:52.000
the right composition.

52:52.000 --> 52:57.000
Everything just right to produce the biggest miracle of all.

52:59.000 --> 53:01.000
Life.

53:01.000 --> 53:07.000
So go ahead, ask, inquire, seek the truth.

53:07.000 --> 53:09.000
It's right that you should know

53:09.000 --> 53:14.000
or the good Lord wouldn't have given you that driving curiosity.

53:14.000 --> 53:18.000
Measure the outside with mathematics,

53:18.000 --> 53:21.000
but measure the inside with prayer.

53:21.000 --> 53:27.000
Prayer is researched to study man as well as the world.

53:27.000 --> 53:29.000
So keep on pitching.

53:29.000 --> 53:32.000
The best is yet to come for you.

53:32.000 --> 53:38.000
I predict man's next great adventure will be the sun age.

53:38.000 --> 53:43.000
When that happens, you'll be rich beyond all dreams.

53:43.000 --> 53:48.000
I predict great sun cities built on desert wastelands

53:48.000 --> 53:52.000
where everything is run by sunlight.

53:52.000 --> 53:54.000
I predict...

53:54.000 --> 53:56.000
Oh, sure, that's fine.

53:56.000 --> 53:59.000
But suppose I begin cutting up, then what?

53:59.000 --> 54:00.000
You won't.

54:00.000 --> 54:04.000
But if you did, man has migrated many times before

54:04.000 --> 54:07.000
and he'll do it again if he has to.

54:07.000 --> 54:11.000
If you make it too hot for him on Earth,

54:11.000 --> 54:15.000
man is capable of conceiving a way to move the whole kitten

54:15.000 --> 54:20.000
to bootle the greener pastures on some other planet.

54:26.000 --> 54:28.000
Oh, no, we like it here.

54:28.000 --> 54:30.000
Don't change on us, Mr. Sun.

54:30.000 --> 54:33.000
We used to worship you as an unknown god.

54:33.000 --> 54:35.000
But now that we know you better,

54:35.000 --> 54:38.000
we love you as our great and good friend.

54:38.000 --> 54:41.000
So keep on shining, Mr. Sun.

54:43.000 --> 54:47.000
Thanks for all the radiant riches you showered down upon us.

54:47.000 --> 54:51.000
Thanks for our eyes and all the glories we behold.

54:51.000 --> 54:54.000
Thanks for all the green forests,

54:54.000 --> 54:57.000
the great deposit of black dimes,

54:57.000 --> 55:02.000
the deep pools of liquid gold you put in the bank for us.

55:02.000 --> 55:04.000
Thanks for the wheat fields,

55:04.000 --> 55:07.000
all the fruits and flowers you grow for us.

55:07.000 --> 55:10.000
Thanks for feeding our animals,

55:10.000 --> 55:13.000
our birds, our insects,

55:13.000 --> 55:15.000
all the fish in the sea.

55:15.000 --> 55:20.000
And thanks especially for the glory and beauty of your good mornings

55:20.000 --> 55:22.000
and your good evenings

55:22.000 --> 55:25.000
and the words of St. Francis.

55:25.000 --> 55:28.000
Be praised, my Lord, in what you have created.

55:28.000 --> 55:33.000
Above all else, be praised in our brother, Master Sun.

